# CAIsat

AI-powered satellite imagery enhancement and object detection on Red Hat OpenShift AI (SwinIR upscaling + YOLOv8-OBB detection).

## Project context

### Layout

- `frontend/` — React app (Three.js globe, Leaflet map, CRA)
- `backend/` — FastAPI enhancement API
- `backend-detection/` — FastAPI detection API
- `chart/` — Helm chart (OpenShift Deployments, Routes, InferenceServices)
- `docs/` — README assets, project plan, spikes, validation

### Tooling

- **Containers**: Podman; project uses `Containerfile` (not Dockerfile)
- **Deploy**: Helm 3 + `oc`; see root `README.md`
- **Pre-commit**: `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (base, python, javascript, markdown, yaml, shell, security, github, container)
- **CI**: `.github/workflows/pre-commit.yaml` — pre-commit + `helm template test ./chart`
- **Push**: `make push` (runs `check` + `helm-template`; refuses `main`/`master`)
- **Handover**: `.cursor/rules/handover.mdc` + this file

### Git remotes

- **upstream**: [rh-ai-quickstart/CAIsat](https://github.com/rh-ai-quickstart/CAIsat) — canonical repo; open PRs here
- **origin**: fork; push feature branches only, never `main`
- PRs deferred; push-as-you-go with `make push`

### Conventions

- Line length 200 (Markdown, YAML, Python via ruff)
- Never commit `.env`, model weights (`*.onnx`, `*.pt`), or secrets
- `scripts/check-no-cluster-info.sh` — pre-commit scan for cluster FQDNs/IPs/personal identifiers

### Docs index

- `README.md` — deploy, architecture, validation
- **`docs/project/PLAN.md`** — **canonical** phase plan, merge gates, spike gates
- `docs/project/PLAN_COMPLETED.md` — archived completed phases
- `docs/spikes/` — spike pass/fail artifacts
- `docs/validation/baseline-smoke.md` — smoke profiles and checklist
- `chart/README.md` — Helm values and templates
- Cursor deep-dive (secondary): `~/.cursor/plans/caisat_comprehensive_review_bde83bb3.plan.md`

